main event: A civilian reported seeing a large whitish ball moving towards Philadelphia, PA on October 10 or 11, 1966.
interesting points: The sighting was reported during the evening at approximately 2000 hours., The observation was made by Mr. J.J. Spotz from Willow Grove Naval Air Station, PA., No physical evidence was documented in the report., The Air Force deemed the data insufficient for evaluation., Follow-up actions included requesting more information from the witness.
witness description: Mr. J.J. Spotz, civilian, Willow Grove Naval Air Station
